# Subordination Agreement

Establishes enforceable priority of claims and liens between senior and junior creditors in a multi-creditor financing.

## Prerequisites

1. **Senior debt documents** with defined terms, debt stack, collateral package, and any agent structure.
2. **Junior/subordinated debt documents** with principal, interest, maturity, security, and amendment history.
3. **Parties and roles** (senior lender/agent, junior lender, borrower, guarantors if applicable).
4. **Collateral description** (UCC, real property, equity interests, or unsecured status).
5. **Governing law/venue** and notice addresses.
6. **Payment rules** (permitted payments, standstill triggers, refinancing treatment).

## Output Structure / Process

1. **Normalize terms** to match the senior credit docs (defined terms, dates, parties, agent/secured party roles).
2. **Populate inputs** using the table below; do not draft until all required fields are known.
3. **Draft the agreement** in the clause order below, inserting schedules where needed.
4. **Run a consistency check** for cross-references, definitions, and payment mechanics.

### Required Inputs

| Item | Required | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Senior Obligations | Yes | Include principal, interest, fees, indemnities, LC/swap, future advances. |
| Junior Obligations | Yes | Include default interest, fees, premiums, costs. |
| Payment in Full | Yes | Cash payment standard, termination of commitments, treatment of contingent obligations. |
| Collateral | Yes | Same collateral, different collateral, or unsecured. |
| Standstill Duration | Yes | Fixed period or until Payment in Full. |
| Permitted Payments | Optional | If allowed, include conditions and suspension triggers. |
| Refinancing Treatment | Yes | Whether replacement senior debt remains senior. |
| Bankruptcy Provisions | Yes | Voting, cash collateral, DIP, turnover. |
| Governing Law/Venue | Yes | Match senior docs unless negotiated. |

### Clause Order Checklist

- [ ] Parties and definitions
- [ ] Recitals (senior facility, junior facility, business rationale)
- [ ] Subordination of payment and liens
- [ ] Standstill and remedies restrictions
- [ ] Turnover/trust of improper payments
- [ ] No contest / no challenge of senior debt or liens
- [ ] Amendments/waivers restrictions (junior docs)
- [ ] Permitted payments (if any)
- [ ] Bankruptcy/insolvency provisions
- [ ] Notices, assignments, successors
- [ ] Governing law, venue, jury waiver
- [ ] Counterparts, electronic signatures
- [ ] Signature blocks and acknowledgment (if required)

### Definitions Table (Minimum Set)

| Defined Term | Must Cover |
| --- | --- |
| Senior Obligations | All amounts due under senior docs, including contingent and future. |
| Junior Obligations | All amounts due under junior docs, including default interest and costs. |
| Payment in Full | Cash payment of all senior obligations and termination of commitments. |
| Collateral | Specific property or all assets; match UCC/real property descriptions. |
| Permitted Payments | Strictly defined amounts and conditions (if allowed). |

### Standstill Matrix

| Trigger | Effect | Notice |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Any senior default | No junior remedies or acceleration | Junior must give prompt notice of junior default |
| Enforcement action by senior | Junior cooperation; no interference | Provide copies of junior notices to senior |
| Bankruptcy filing | Junior votes/acts consistent with senior | Confirm proof of claim treatment |

### Permitted Payments Template (If Used)

```text
Permitted Payments. So long as (a) no Senior Default exists or is continuing,
(b) Borrower delivers a compliance certificate dated within 5 Business Days,
and (c) such payment is not from Collateral proceeds, Borrower may pay
[interest only] on the Junior Obligations on regularly scheduled due dates.
Any violation is subject to immediate turnover.
```

### Turnover Provision Requirements

- Payments received in violation are held in trust for senior creditor.
- Immediate delivery of cash or property to senior creditor.
- Applies regardless of knowledge or characterization of payment.

### Bankruptcy/Insovlency Minimums

- Subordination enforceable in bankruptcy (11 U.S.C. § 510(a)) [VERIFY]
- Junior agrees not to oppose senior cash collateral/DIP financing
- Voting alignment or proxy in favor of senior-supported plan
- Turnover of bankruptcy distributions until Payment in Full

### Schedules/Exhibits (Use if applicable)

```text
Schedule 1: Senior Debt Documents (date, parties, title)
Schedule 2: Junior Debt Documents (date, parties, title)
Exhibit A: Collateral Description
Exhibit B: Notice Addresses
```

## Guidelines

- Match senior-doc defined terms exactly; avoid redefinition drift.
- If junior debt is secured, confirm lien priority and any subordination filings.
- Treat refinancing as Senior Obligations unless expressly excluded.
- Make standstill and turnover provisions unambiguous and self-executing.
- Include agent/administrative agent language where senior debt is syndicated.
- Ensure jury waiver is conspicuous if required by jurisdiction.
- If real property liens are subordinated, include recording/acknowledgment formalities.
- Avoid provisions that attempt to waive non-waivable bankruptcy rights; flag for review.
